<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="91" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[140,1107,1398,1672]" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1911" box="[188,327,1504,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Placusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vaga">
<emphasis box="[188,327,1504,1530]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Placusa vaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is newly recorded from the 
<collectingRegion box="[643,889,1504,1530]" country="Canada" name="Northwest Territories" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Northwest Territories</collectingRegion>
. Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[140,221,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Placusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[140,221,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Placusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
live in subcortical habitats in scolytine burrows where they apparently feed on fungal hyphae. In 
<collectingRegion box="[384,475,1574,1600]" country="Canada" name="Quebec" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Québec</collectingRegion>
, specimens were collected in balsam fir (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1768" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" box="[932,1063,1574,1601]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balsamea">
<emphasis box="[932,1063,1574,1601]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">A. balsamea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), white spruce (
<taxonomicName authority="(Moench) Voss" authorityName="Voss" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Moench" box="[299,615,1610,1637]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glauca">
<emphasis box="[299,433,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Picea glauca</emphasis>
(Moench) Voss
</taxonomicName>
), and mixed white spruce-trembling aspen (
<taxonomicName authority="Michx." authorityName="Michx." box="[149,454,1645,1672]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tremuloides">
<emphasis box="[149,364,1645,1671]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="91">Populus tremuloides</emphasis>
Michx.
</taxonomicName>
) stands (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[553,839,1645,1671]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Klimaszewski" pageId="6" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 47" refId="ref15598" refString="Klimaszewski J, Pelletier G, Germain C, Hebert C, Humble LM, Winchester NM (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae, Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomologist 133: 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">Klimaszewski et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
